KaTeX (bundled webview assets — media/katex/)
---------------------------------------------
The math-preview webview renders LaTeX with KaTeX. Its distribution files
(`katex.min.js`, `katex.min.css`, and the `KaTeX_*` woff2 web fonts) are
vendored verbatim under `media/katex/` and shipped inside the `.vsix`; they are
loaded only inside the preview webview, never into the extension host.

  https://github.com/KaTeX/KaTeX
  License: MIT
  Pinned: katex 0.16.x (see the `katex` devDependency in package.json)

Vendored copy provenance: copied from `node_modules/katex/dist/` after
`npm install`. Only the woff2 fonts are shipped (the CSS lists woff2 first and
the webview's Chromium picks it; the woff/ttf faces are omitted to keep the
package lean). To refresh, re-copy `katex.min.js`, `katex.min.css`, and
`fonts/*.woff2` from the pinned dist and re-verify the MIT license still holds.

Mermaid (bundled webview asset — media/mermaid/)
------------------------------------------------
The diagram-preview webview renders Mermaid (```` ```{mermaid} ````) diagrams
with the Mermaid library. A single, self-contained distribution file
(`mermaid.min.js`) is vendored verbatim under `media/mermaid/` and shipped inside
the `.vsix`; it is loaded only inside the preview webview, never into the
extension host.

  https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid
  License: MIT (Copyright (c) 2014 - 2022 Knut Sveidqvist)
  Pinned: mermaid 11.16.0
  File: dist/mermaid.min.js (sha256
        74d7c46dabca328c2294733910a8aa1ed0c37451776e8d5295da38a2b758fb9b)

Vendored copy provenance: extracted from the npm registry tarball
https://registry.npmjs.org/mermaid/-/mermaid-11.16.0.tgz (`package/dist/
mermaid.min.js`). Unlike KaTeX, Mermaid is NOT added as a devDependency: the
distribution file is a single self-contained UMD bundle (it exposes
`globalThis.mermaid`, performs no runtime `import()`, and needs no
`'unsafe-eval'`), so only this one file ships and pulling Mermaid's large
transitive dev-dependency tree into `node_modules` solely to copy it is
unnecessary. To refresh, re-download the pinned (or newer) tarball, verify the
MIT license still holds, copy `dist/mermaid.min.js`, and update the version +
sha256 above. Graphviz (`{dot}`) cells are detected but not yet rendered (their
source is shown) — rendering them needs a separate WASM renderer, vendored in a
future slice.

On upgrade of any referenced grammar or tool, re-verify the license still holds
at the pinned version and update this file (architecture plan §9, §14).
